The UN proposed yesterday in Cancún a plan to restore domestic lighting, lighting trade and industrial space in 100 countries with a view to achieving a greenhouse effect reduction (GES), which corresponds to almost one-third of the next limit to be achieved for the stability of the planet's climate from now until 2020.
