These funds are, under the Copenhagen Agreement, 'new and additional' to ensure that the increased burden is realized without prejudice to the public development assistance.
Unfortunately, there's no consensus on what "new and additional" means.
While the European Commission proposed harmonisation, some Member States, including France, blocked the process.
Today, everyone chooses the reference that suits him best.
